00:47:40.657 --> 00:47:44.340
does actually have an effect on
how parents treat children.

00:47:44.340 --> 00:47:49.800
You'll see girls treated better
in places where tea is

00:47:49.800 --> 00:47:53.720
the cash crop or something and
the price increases, versus

00:47:53.720 --> 00:47:55.680
areas where tea is not
the cash crop,

00:47:55.680 --> 00:47:57.150
but the price increases.

00:47:57.150 --> 00:47:59.600
There shouldn't be a change in
how the girls are treated.

00:47:59.600 --> 00:48:00.090
PROFESSOR: Correct.

00:48:00.090 --> 00:48:04.220
So we're going to compare years
when tea prices went up

00:48:04.220 --> 00:48:09.100
with years when tea prices
didn't go up and compare them

00:48:09.100 --> 00:48:13.010
in areas where tea is a
plausible crop and areas where

00:48:13.010 --> 00:48:15.770
tea cannot be grown.

00:48:15.770 --> 00:48:18.800
So the increase in tea prices
should have no effect where

00:48:18.800 --> 00:48:21.100
tea cannot be grown.

00:48:21.100 --> 00:48:23.760
It will have a spurious
effect, maybe,

00:48:23.760 --> 00:48:24.850
but no really effect.

00:48:24.850 --> 00:48:26.620
It should have an effect
where tea can be grown.

00:48:26.620 --> 00:48:32.010
So we're going to compare tea
possible areas with other

00:48:32.010 --> 00:48:35.542
areas, when tea prices go up
versus when it doesn't.

00:48:35.542 --> 00:48:36.150
Yeah?

00:48:36.150 --> 00:48:38.278
AUDIENCE: How about we think
about it just like you have

00:48:38.278 --> 00:48:42.613
you control population, where
the tea price going up

00:48:42.613 --> 00:48:43.245
shouldn't have an effect.

00:48:43.245 --> 00:48:45.661
And then you have your
non-control, and you just take

00:48:45.661 --> 00:48:47.866
you data and subtract your
control from it to see you

00:48:47.866 --> 00:48:48.310
[INAUDIBLE].

00:48:48.310 --> 00:48:49.630
PROFESSOR: That's
exactly right.

00:48:49.630 --> 00:48:51.950
So that's another way to
say the same thing.

00:48:51.950 --> 00:48:54.840
Anybody else want to add
anything to that?

00:48:54.840 --> 00:48:58.040
So let me show you
some trends.

00:48:58.040 --> 00:49:01.950
So that's the basic fact.

00:49:01.950 --> 00:49:06.430
So that's tea prices.

00:49:06.430 --> 00:49:10.400
Suddenly in '79, you see stock
tea prices just skyrocketed.

00:49:10.400 --> 00:49:12.820
That's the first fact.

00:49:12.820 --> 00:49:14.420
Tea prices are going up.

00:49:14.420 --> 00:49:16.360
Tea production is going up.

00:49:16.360 --> 00:49:20.150
Second thing is that if you
look at tea versus other

00:49:20.150 --> 00:49:23.510
crops, tea prices are going up
faster than other crops.

00:49:23.510 --> 00:49:25.400
So other crops are like grain.

00:49:25.400 --> 00:49:29.070
Grain is going up, but tea
is going up faster.

00:49:29.070 --> 00:49:31.830
Oil is going up, but tea
is going up faster.

00:49:31.830 --> 00:49:33.560
So tea is the crop
that is going up

00:49:33.560 --> 00:49:37.750
fastest among these crops.

00:49:37.750 --> 00:49:39.450
Look at this one.

00:49:39.450 --> 00:49:42.680
Here we're comparing
fruits with tea.

00:49:42.680 --> 00:49:45.000
And fruits are going
up much faster.

00:49:45.000 --> 00:49:50.180
Fruits with other crops, like
grain, oil, and cotton, and

00:49:50.180 --> 00:49:52.310
again, fruits are going
up much faster.

00:49:52.310 --> 00:49:57.360
So basically, what matters is
not the absolute price.

00:49:57.360 --> 00:50:02.410
The relative price matters,
because it's what makes you

00:50:02.410 --> 00:50:04.280
want to do more tea.

00:50:04.280 --> 00:50:07.330
So tea areas are benefiting,
relative to those other areas.

00:50:13.190 --> 00:50:15.010
So this is a complicated
graph, so

00:50:15.010 --> 00:50:16.560
let's do this slowly.

00:50:16.560 --> 00:50:19.010
Try to understand what's
in this graph.

00:50:19.010 --> 00:50:27.690
So what's in this graph is areas
which grow a lot of tea.

00:50:35.240 --> 00:50:38.055
This is the coefficient
in the regression.

00:50:41.610 --> 00:50:49.080
So this is the effect of having
more area devoted to

00:50:49.080 --> 00:50:50.970
tea in a particular year.

00:50:50.970 --> 00:51:00.490
So what this is saying is that
before 1979, you see tea

00:51:00.490 --> 00:51:01.650
prices are low.

00:51:01.650 --> 00:51:07.260
In those years, if you look at
the fraction of males, the

00:51:07.260 --> 00:51:09.510
fraction of males
bounces around.

00:51:09.510 --> 00:51:16.800
But the fact that tea is sown
has essentially very close to

00:51:16.800 --> 00:51:19.110
zero effect.

00:51:19.110 --> 00:51:23.040
After 1979, the fact that
tea is sown has

00:51:23.040 --> 00:51:23.980
a much bigger effect.

00:51:23.980 --> 00:51:28.950
So this is the effect of how
much land you put into tea in

00:51:28.950 --> 00:51:31.660
a particular year,
so year by year.

00:51:31.660 --> 00:51:39.470
So in that year, what's
happening, in 1983, how many

00:51:39.470 --> 00:51:46.800
boys versus girls were born
in high tea areas

00:51:46.800 --> 00:51:48.410
relative to low tea areas?

00:51:48.410 --> 00:51:50.150
That's always the exercise.

00:51:50.150 --> 00:51:56.480
So think of one more percent
of land devoted to tea.

00:51:56.480 --> 00:52:00.920
What is the effect of that
on the fraction of

00:52:00.920 --> 00:52:04.940
boys born in 1983?

00:52:04.940 --> 00:52:07.430
That's what that says.

00:52:07.430 --> 00:52:11.300
So the main point to take
away is you see a

00:52:11.300 --> 00:52:15.110
big drop after 1979.

00:52:15.110 --> 00:52:21.740
So tea areas, the fraction of
boys born goes down right when

00:52:21.740 --> 00:52:22.850
you think it should go down.

00:52:22.850 --> 00:52:24.637
It is when the price
starts going up.

00:52:27.380 --> 00:52:30.730
So that's what this is saying.

00:52:30.730 --> 00:52:35.390
Before that, the average
is kind of at 0.15.

00:52:35.390 --> 00:52:39.720
After that, the average
is about 0.35.

00:52:39.720 --> 00:52:44.650
So the fraction of boys goes
down after the change.

00:52:44.650 --> 00:52:49.130
This is what happens in
the fruit areas--

00:52:49.130 --> 00:52:51.510
the opposite.

00:52:51.510 --> 00:52:55.330
After '79, fruit prices
go up also a lot.

00:52:55.330 --> 00:52:56.580
And fruit favors boys.

00:52:59.600 --> 00:53:02.170
The ratio used to be lower.

00:53:02.170 --> 00:53:04.992
It goes up afterwards.

00:53:04.992 --> 00:53:05.483
Yeah?

00:53:05.483 --> 00:53:06.956
AUDIENCE: Are these significant
results?

00:53:06.956 --> 00:53:10.910
PROFESSOR: Yes, so the average
is significantly different.

00:53:10.910 --> 00:53:11.850
You're right.

00:53:11.850 --> 00:53:14.230
Year by year, they're
not significant.

00:53:14.230 --> 00:53:16.930
But that's because it's a
small sample of people.

00:53:16.930 --> 00:53:21.580
But if you take the average of
these periods, the averages

00:53:21.580 --> 00:53:22.900
are significantly different.

00:53:22.900 --> 00:53:25.470
AUDIENCE: I'm just having
trouble understanding how so

00:53:25.470 --> 00:53:36.809
if women are better at picking
tea leaves, the economics make

00:53:36.809 --> 00:53:40.753
sense, but I can't see families
consciously choosing

00:53:40.753 --> 00:53:44.600
to have more girls.

00:53:44.600 --> 00:53:47.720
In 12 years, they'll
begin to--

00:53:47.720 --> 00:53:49.290
PROFESSOR: Well, yes and no.

00:53:49.290 --> 00:53:50.450
You're right with that.

00:53:50.450 --> 00:53:52.910
But on the other hand, it also
sends a signal which reminds

00:53:52.910 --> 00:53:55.750
them, oh well, you know.

00:53:55.750 --> 00:53:56.420
Two things--

00:53:56.420 --> 00:53:59.280
one, you might imagine that
the women might be more

00:53:59.280 --> 00:54:03.780
pro-girls, plausibly.

00:54:03.780 --> 00:54:07.240
And if you think that
women income share

00:54:07.240 --> 00:54:08.440
goes up in the family--

00:54:08.440 --> 00:54:09.800
AUDIENCE: They have
more stakes.

00:54:09.800 --> 00:54:10.610
PROFESSOR: They have more say.

00:54:10.610 --> 00:54:12.530
So that's one possible
mechanism.

00:54:12.530 --> 00:54:19.780
The second mechanism is just
that maybe when girls' incomes

00:54:19.780 --> 00:54:27.330
go up, they just look at it and
say, well, after all, all

00:54:27.330 --> 00:54:28.770
the women are working
these days.

00:54:28.770 --> 00:54:30.090
Why not have another girl?

00:54:30.090 --> 00:54:31.620
They'll be fine.

00:54:31.620 --> 00:54:34.540
They'll find a job as well.

00:54:34.540 --> 00:54:37.880
I can't tell what's going
on at that level.

00:54:37.880 --> 00:54:40.040
But it's clear that this
result is significant.

00:54:40.040 --> 00:54:41.290
It's actually substantial.

00:54:45.550 --> 00:54:48.070
Final set of thoughts--

00:54:52.150 --> 00:54:53.400
suppose this goes on.

00:54:56.085 --> 00:54:57.990
Let me back up.

00:54:57.990 --> 00:54:59.415
What's going on?

00:54:59.415 --> 00:55:01.245
How are they losing
all these girls?

00:55:01.245 --> 00:55:06.330
If it's an economic mechanism,
that says that there is

00:55:06.330 --> 00:55:08.360
incentive to lose the girls.

00:55:08.360 --> 00:55:11.340
How are they actually
doing it?

00:55:11.340 --> 00:55:12.590
What's going on?

00:55:19.754 --> 00:55:24.160
Unfortunately, it's all not very
nice, what's going on.

00:55:24.160 --> 00:55:26.250
So two things are happening.

00:55:26.250 --> 00:55:30.750
One is basically the technology
for pre-birth

00:55:30.750 --> 00:55:34.530
detection of gender of the
child has improved a lot.

00:55:37.160 --> 00:55:41.690
If you do amniocentesis, which
is an expensive procedure, you

00:55:41.690 --> 00:55:44.550
can basically very high
probability predict the gender

00:55:44.550 --> 00:55:46.070
of the child.

00:55:46.070 --> 00:55:50.380
The reason why rich areas are
doing the worst is precisely

00:55:50.380 --> 00:55:51.120
because of that.

00:55:51.120 --> 00:55:53.345
Rich areas are using
this technology.

00:55:56.000 --> 00:55:59.320
It's an expensive technology.

00:55:59.320 --> 00:56:02.230
You spend money to use it.

00:56:02.230 --> 00:56:06.830
You see in like the richer parts
of India, signs up would

00:56:06.830 --> 00:56:15.030
say, would you rather
spend basically $100

00:56:15.030 --> 00:56:22.380
now or $10,000 later?

00:56:22.380 --> 00:56:25.660
The idea is that you're to give
dowry for your daughter

00:56:25.660 --> 00:56:26.720
to get her married.

00:56:26.720 --> 00:56:28.000
And that's your cost.

00:56:28.000 --> 00:56:33.190
And so you should really get
ready to spend, whatever, $100

00:56:33.190 --> 00:56:37.460
now, identify her,
and then have an

00:56:37.460 --> 00:56:40.380
abortion, rather than spend.

00:56:40.380 --> 00:56:41.960
You see these signs up.

00:56:41.960 --> 00:56:44.000
They're all the illegal.

00:56:44.000 --> 00:56:46.450
Amniocentesis about eight
years ago was

00:56:46.450 --> 00:56:48.490
made illegal in India.

00:56:48.490 --> 00:56:51.010
It's still completely
prevalent.

00:56:51.010 --> 00:56:55.420
And since people are willing
to try to have many babies,

00:56:55.420 --> 00:57:00.240
they're even willing to do
it by using a much weaker

00:57:00.240 --> 00:57:01.750
technology, which
is a sonography.

00:57:01.750 --> 00:57:06.280
Sonography, which is a
technology that is legal, it

00:57:06.280 --> 00:57:09.760
doesn't identify the gender of
the child all the time, but

00:57:09.760 --> 00:57:12.060
over 25% of the time, it does.

00:57:12.060 --> 00:57:16.040
And when it does, then you can
immediately abort the child.

00:57:16.040 --> 00:57:18.900
So they're using technologies
to identify.

00:57:18.900 --> 00:57:21.650
This is why this is happening
more in richer areas, because

00:57:21.650 --> 00:57:23.390
technologies cost money.

00:57:23.390 --> 00:57:27.030
And the poorest areas are ones
where the technology is least

00:57:27.030 --> 00:57:29.580
used, because it's
just expensive.

00:57:29.580 --> 00:57:35.190
So you see basically a very,
very clear correlation between

00:57:35.190 --> 00:57:37.980
where the technology arrives
and the fraction

00:57:37.980 --> 00:57:40.390
of boys being born.

00:57:40.390 --> 00:57:42.210
So that's one thing
that's going on.

00:57:42.210 --> 00:57:46.370
Second thing is going on almost
surely is a lot of

00:57:46.370 --> 00:57:51.730
post-birth, I think, murder is
the only word you could use.

00:57:51.730 --> 00:57:54.250
I think unfortunately there's
a lot of, I think, children

00:57:54.250 --> 00:57:56.820
being disposed of.

00:57:56.820 --> 00:58:00.900
There are villages which report
to have, probably

00:58:00.900 --> 00:58:04.110
report, there's a news report I
think from like the Chinese

00:58:04.110 --> 00:58:12.220
news agency which says that we
haven't had a girl born in our

00:58:12.220 --> 00:58:13.900
village in the last
five years.

00:58:13.900 --> 00:58:17.370
There's a news report of the
village chief proudly

00:58:17.370 --> 00:58:21.400
announcing that there was no
girl born in his village in

00:58:21.400 --> 00:58:22.140
the last five years.

00:58:22.140 --> 00:58:25.940
So I think there is a lot of
just direct, deliberate action

00:58:25.940 --> 00:58:27.860
going on there.

00:58:27.860 --> 00:58:32.540
Now, there are many things
to think about here.

00:58:32.540 --> 00:58:33.350
How do you stop it?

00:58:33.350 --> 00:58:34.430
The government has tried.

00:58:34.430 --> 00:58:37.210
It tried to have technologies.

00:58:37.210 --> 00:58:39.905
There's a bunch of programs
around now, for example.

00:58:42.460 --> 00:58:45.860
India has a number of states
where they have programs that

00:58:45.860 --> 00:58:51.580
basically promise parents a
certain amount of money if

00:58:51.580 --> 00:58:54.380
your girl graduates
from high school--

00:58:54.380 --> 00:58:55.350
quite a lot of money.

00:58:55.350 --> 00:58:56.640
So that's one way
to [INAUDIBLE]

00:58:56.640 --> 00:58:59.560
incentives based on
girls' arrival.

00:59:06.870 --> 00:59:10.000
But it's not clear how
well that works.

00:59:10.000 --> 00:59:15.200
Because in some ways, it's
something that's based on 20

00:59:15.200 --> 00:59:15.940
years later.

00:59:15.940 --> 00:59:19.540
And you don't necessarily think
that people are that

00:59:19.540 --> 00:59:21.870
responsive to it.

00:59:21.870 --> 00:59:24.530
The other thing you can think
about is is there any economic

00:59:24.530 --> 00:59:32.090
force that this, by itself, sets
off, which will then make

00:59:32.090 --> 00:59:33.340
re-equilibrium.

00:59:33.340 --> 00:59:36.910
So one issue that arises is
what's happening to the

00:59:36.910 --> 00:59:38.150
marriage market?

00:59:38.150 --> 00:59:39.150
So what do you think
will happen to the

00:59:39.150 --> 00:59:44.484
marriage market in China?

00:59:44.484 --> 00:59:47.340
AUDIENCE: Well, if there are
fewer women, then each one is

00:59:47.340 --> 00:59:49.250
essentially worth more.

00:59:49.250 --> 00:59:50.500
PROFESSOR: Yeah.

00:59:53.290 --> 00:59:56.570
Dowry should go down, and bride
price should go up.

01:00:05.600 --> 01:00:08.540
Why this hasn't happened already
in India, especially,

01:00:08.540 --> 01:00:11.170
is that men tend to marry
women who are

01:00:11.170 --> 01:00:13.914
younger than them.

01:00:13.914 --> 01:00:18.930
If the population is growing,
and people marry women who are

01:00:18.930 --> 01:00:28.790
younger than them, then even if
there are fewer girls born,

01:00:28.790 --> 01:00:33.640
the girls are from a different
cohort, from a younger cohort.

01:00:33.640 --> 01:00:36.830
So the population is growing, so
there's more girls around.

01:00:41.220 --> 01:00:42.630
So that's one problem.

01:00:42.630 --> 01:00:44.750
This force might operate,
but only if

01:00:44.750 --> 01:00:46.110
population growth stops.

01:00:46.110 --> 01:00:48.640
So it's going to operate more in
China where the population

01:00:48.640 --> 01:00:51.170
growth has stopped than in India
where the population

01:00:51.170 --> 01:00:52.800
growth is still going on.

01:00:52.800 --> 01:00:54.810
As long as there's population
growth, you're going to see

01:00:54.810 --> 01:00:57.975
this possibility of just going
down in the cohort chain.

01:01:01.200 --> 01:01:04.430
So you might imagine that the
price of girls will go up, but

01:01:04.430 --> 01:01:08.850
it won't go up if people marry
much younger women.

01:01:08.850 --> 01:01:10.340
That's one issue.

01:01:10.340 --> 01:01:17.830
Second issue, so in China, one
of things that people are

01:01:17.830 --> 01:01:20.750
often puzzled about
is what's going on

01:01:20.750 --> 01:01:22.000
with the savings rate?

01:01:24.750 --> 01:01:27.910
The savings rate in China,
personal savings, is

01:01:27.910 --> 01:01:29.830
historically unprecedented.

01:01:29.830 --> 01:01:34.602
People save 30% of their
incomes, as it is compared to

01:01:34.602 --> 01:01:38.760
the US, which used to save zero
till recently, and after

01:01:38.760 --> 01:01:42.090
the crisis has gone up to 7%.

01:01:42.090 --> 01:01:46.300
So personal savings rates
in China are massive.

01:01:46.300 --> 01:01:49.700
So one puzzle people have often
been thinking about is

01:01:49.700 --> 01:01:51.980
what's going on with that?

01:01:51.980 --> 01:01:54.170
There's a very nice paper which
does the following.

01:01:56.680 --> 01:02:03.110
If I look at areas which have
high gender ratios, where

01:02:03.110 --> 01:02:08.890
women are really scarce,
are people saving

01:02:08.890 --> 01:02:11.690
more in those areas?

01:02:11.690 --> 01:02:12.940
Why would they save more?

01:02:17.310 --> 01:02:22.270
Why would you save more if
you're a parent of boy?

01:02:22.270 --> 01:02:25.520
So he particularly asked, if
you're a parent of a boy, in

01:02:25.520 --> 01:02:27.800
China it's easy, because
people have one child.

01:02:27.800 --> 01:02:29.760
So they're either a parent of
a boy or parent of a girl.

01:02:29.760 --> 01:02:34.040
If you're parent of a boy in an
area where the gender ratio

01:02:34.040 --> 01:02:39.190
is particularly bad, so very
few girls, it turns

01:02:39.190 --> 01:02:40.700
out you save more.

01:02:40.700 --> 01:02:41.950
Why would that be the case?

01:02:46.062 --> 01:02:47.470
AUDIENCE: The price
of a bride.

01:02:47.470 --> 01:02:50.350
PROFESSOR: Yeah, you have
to buy your son a bride.

01:02:50.350 --> 01:02:52.160
So people are saving more.

01:02:52.160 --> 01:02:55.720
So basically they suggest that
people are beginning to save

01:02:55.720 --> 01:03:00.760
more in order to buy their
child a bride.

01:03:00.760 --> 01:03:02.840
And the way you buy it
is you don't go and

01:03:02.840 --> 01:03:03.960
buy her in the market.

01:03:03.960 --> 01:03:07.020
But basically women have become
very picky about not

01:03:07.020 --> 01:03:11.040
marrying into families, which
can't afford to give their son

01:03:11.040 --> 01:03:18.380
a separate apartment to move
into when they get married.

01:03:18.380 --> 01:03:20.450
China has very poor
mortgage markets.

01:03:20.450 --> 01:03:24.230
So you can't really take out
a mortgage to buy a house.

01:03:24.230 --> 01:03:26.670
So the only you buy a house is
you borrow from your parents.

01:03:26.670 --> 01:03:28.450
Your parents give you a gift.

01:03:28.450 --> 01:03:32.520
So parents now, it's become a
status issue for parents to

01:03:32.520 --> 01:03:33.920
marry this sons.

01:03:33.920 --> 01:03:37.190
And the way you marry your son
is by buying him an apartment

01:03:37.190 --> 01:03:38.640
when he gets married.

01:03:38.640 --> 01:03:40.550
So if you don't have
enough wealth, you

01:03:40.550 --> 01:03:41.720
can't buy an apartment.

01:03:41.720 --> 01:03:43.610
And then your son can't
get married.

01:03:43.610 --> 01:03:49.410
So this seems to be sort of one
of the facts that might

01:03:49.410 --> 01:03:52.520
actually re-equilibriate China,
because it seems like

01:03:52.520 --> 01:03:56.390
one thing that's going on in
China right now is this

01:03:56.390 --> 01:03:58.035
massive increase in savings.

01:04:00.900 --> 01:04:04.560
The problem with this method in
increasing savings is it's

01:04:04.560 --> 01:04:06.490
a zero sum game.

01:04:06.490 --> 01:04:08.370
There are only so many girls.

01:04:08.370 --> 01:04:13.890
So the fact that I'm saving a
lot for my son just means my

01:04:13.890 --> 01:04:16.680
