not anybody else.

01:04:16.680 --> 01:04:18.220
It's not now that the number
of women go up

01:04:18.220 --> 01:04:19.880
because they save.

01:04:19.880 --> 01:04:23.150
So this is not really
solving the problem.

01:04:23.150 --> 01:04:25.920
It's squeezing parents.

01:04:25.920 --> 01:04:30.870
So if I were to save $1 more in
order to buy my son a house

01:04:30.870 --> 01:04:35.010
so he can get married, then
somebody else is going to want

01:04:35.010 --> 01:04:35.890
to do the same thing.

01:04:35.890 --> 01:04:38.650
He's going to try to save even
more than me and buy a house

01:04:38.650 --> 01:04:40.160
for his son.

01:04:40.160 --> 01:04:44.050
So that competition is a
very kind of a negative

01:04:44.050 --> 01:04:44.880
competition.

01:04:44.880 --> 01:04:47.810
Everybody's getting hurt
by that competition.

01:04:47.810 --> 01:04:53.700
So that should make parents
really rethink this strategy.

01:04:53.700 --> 01:04:57.230
The one sign of hope I see is
this one, which is the market

01:04:57.230 --> 01:05:00.390
forces seem to be kind
of operating to make

01:05:00.390 --> 01:05:01.430
this problem better.

